  m_Name: Parlor
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Parlor
  description: "The parlor, or \u201CHerenkamer,\u201D was a formal reception room
    in wealthy households where the male head of the family would entertain guests,
    conduct business, and display status. It was often furnished with expensive items
    such as fine seating, decorative cabinets, games, and drinking accessories. The
    room was designed to impress visitors and reflect the wealth, education, and
    social standing of the household."
  illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: ce3b2aedbbf76d741b24de8375b8e13f, type: 3}
